<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10491617>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Cymbasoma pedroisp.nov.from north-west Iceland,adult female holotype;ventral view of whole specimen.Image from confocal laser scanning microscopy (CLSM).Abbreviations:1-4, purported position of antennule segments 1-4; antennule; as, anal somite; bs, basipodal seta; cr, furcal ramus; exs, terminal exopodal spine; gs, genital somite; oc, oral cone; ovs, ovigerous spines; P1-P4, legs 1-4. Asterisk indicates anteriorly produced forehead." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10491617/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10491619>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Cymbasoma pedroi from off North-west Iceland, adult female holotype. (a) cephalothorax, dorsal view; (b) urosome and fifth legs, lateral view; (c) urosome, dorsal view; (d) urosome and fifth legs, ventral view; (e) distal part of fused fifth leg ramus. Abbreviations: as, anal somite; bs, basal seta; con, lateral constriction; enp, endopod lobe; exp, exopod lobe; exs, terminal exopodal spine; fh, forehead; gs, genital somite; ovs, ovigerous spines; st, suture; str, striae. Arrows in (b), (c) and (d) indicate posterolateral protuberances of genital double-somite. Scale bars: a–d = 100 μm, e = 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10491619/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

